    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1962-03-24T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1962-03-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="110"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d110">
                <head>110. Telegram From the Station in the Congo to the Central Intelligence
                        Agency<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d110fn1">Source: Central
                        Intelligence Agency Files, Job 78–00435R, DDO/ISS Files, Box 1, Folder 9,
                            [<hi rend="italic">cryptonym not declassified</hi>] Operations. Secret;
                        No Night Action; <gloss target="#t_Rybat_1">Rybat</gloss>; [<hi
                            rend="italic">cryptonym not declassified</hi>]; Operational Immediate.
                        Received at 1106Z.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Leopoldville</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1962-03-24">March 24, 1962</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3470 (In 48189). 1. [<persName corresp="#p_IDE_1">Identity 1</persName>]
                    requested one million <gloss target="#t_BCF_1">BCF</gloss> [<hi rend="italic"
                        >less than 1 line not declassified</hi>] said [<persName corresp="#p_IDE_1"
                        >Identity 2</persName>] and [<persName corresp="#p_IDE_1">Identity
                        3</persName>] have decided make all-out effort split and weaken extremist
                    political ranks in Orientale just as [<hi rend="italic">cryptonym not
                        declassified</hi>] have done in Leop. Said extremists making strong bid for
                    regaining political control in Orientale and [<persName corresp="#p_IDE_1"
                        >Identity 2</persName>] wants head them off. [<persName corresp="#p_IDE_1"
                        >Identity 1</persName>] commented extremists <pb facs="0184" n="151"
                        xml:id="pg_151"/> now lack capable leader and thus [<hi rend="italic"
                        >cryptonym not declassified</hi>] stand good chance accomplishing their
                        objective.<note n="2" xml:id="d110fn2">
                        <gloss target="#t_CIA_1">CIA</gloss> telegram 49712 to Leopoldville, March
                        24, approved the requested expenditure. (Ibid.)</note>
                </p>
                <p>[Omitted here is further discussion of the plan.]</p>
            </div>
        </body>
